\": 635, \"to\": 699, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We were a moment away from a 'please clap',\\\" quipped a third.\", \"from\": 701, \"to\": 763, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Continuing the pun, another branded him \\\"inseinely brave\\\" for cracking the joke.\", \"from\": 764, \"to\": 844, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It comes after multiple athletes fell ill following their Olympic swims in the famous Seine, leading to fears that they may have been exposed to E.coli bacteria in the water.\", \"from\": 846, \"to\": 1020, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 932, \"end\": 937, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 0.9999991437493037, \"rank\": 8.562505615864154e-07, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"On Sunday, it emerged that three athletes from the German team were treated as hospital outpatientsafter suffering nausea, vomitting and diarrhea.\", \"from\": 1021, \"to\": 1167, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1072, \"end\": 1078, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/German_language\", \"score\": 0.9741405302993335, \"rank\": 0.026532063309779794, \"text\": \"German\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/German_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/German_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"READ MORE:Hazel Irvine's remarks cause Olympics frenzy as fans make Andrew Cotter demand  nothing has ever been louder in this universe than Andrew Cotter's \\\"Ugh.\\\"\", \"from\": 1169, \"to\": 1332, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1237, \"end\": 1250, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andrew_Cotter\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Andrew Cotter\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andrew_Cotter\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andrew_Cotter\"}, {\"begin\": 1310, \"end\": 1323,